Date:	12/01/2006
Name:	(g)WebcppUI
Ver.:	2.0.1
Author:	Jeffrey Bakker
Email:	seeplusplus@users.sourceforge.net
Web:	http://webcpp.sf.net


Instructions:
Just untar/extract webcppui to a local folder, and run `./webcppui` in the
folder to start WebcppUI


Notes:
It's been years since I've worked on this project, but it's time for a new
significant release. This is not just a new version of Webcpp GtkGui, this
is a complete rewrite and port of the WebcppUI tool for Windows. It is not
only a GUI for webcpp, but also a GUI for MkScs2 - for making webcpp colour
schemes. Unlike previous versions of Gtk+ webcpp GUIs, this is developed in
python and libglade for rapid development.


Requirements:
Gtk+ 2.4 or higher, python, pygtk 2.6, webcpp 0.8.2 or higher.


Description:
WebcppUI is a Gtk+ interface for Webcpp and MkScs2, providing a unified user
environment for creating webcpp commands and designing webcpp syntax colour
schemes.

Webcpp is a cross-platform utility software which converts programmer's source
code into highlighted HTML code. This software supports over 30 programming
languages and runs on Windows and many UNIX variants, including Linux.


Thanks:
To Pádraig Brady for the GladeWrapper library. It is extremely useful, and has
made my transition from programming GTK+ in C to using python/libglade seem to
be almost effortless.
